From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Marco Borrini <borrinimarco74@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 26 May 2026 09:00:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 1/1] Do not redefine inline

Redefining inline as __attribute__((__always_inline__)) breaks standard
headers like Mingw-w64's inttypes.h which rely on the inline keyword for
__CRT_INLINE. Modern compilers handle inlining heuristics well enough
without forcing always_inline globally.

--- a/configure.ac
+++ b/configure.ac
@@ -102,7 +102,7 @@
 
 dnl Checks for typedefs, structures, and compiler characteristics.
 AC_C_CONST
-AC_C_ALWAYS_INLINE
+AC_C_INLINE
 AC_C_RESTRICT
 AC_C_BUILTIN_EXPECT
 AC_C_BIGENDIAN
